{
  "abstract": "A mycoparasite, Fusor~urn longipes Wollenw. and Reinking, parasitizing Sclerospora graminicola,\r\nthat causes downy mildew of pearl 'millet is reported. The mycoparasite attacks only downy mildew-infected\r\nareas of the leaves. The mycoparasite produces brownish spots with variable sizes and may cover the entire\r\ninfected leaf under humid conditions resulting in the complete inhibition of sporangial produc~ion. Such plants\r\nare killed immaturely. Attempts to selectively control the mycoparasite by the use of fungicide or to identify\r\ngenotypes which can support S. graminicola but not F. longipes have been unsuccessful",
